<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-26T03:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-26T03:30:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/62401/3:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-26T10:30:00+02:00">October 26, 1940—10:30 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 26—8:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>824. Department’s triple priority 637, October 25, 2 p.m. I delivered
                                the message personally to the Marshal at 10:15 a.m. this morning.
                                The text transmitted through Henry-Haye has not yet been
                                received.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>